HEADWORD: adrenocorticotropin
<hw>adrenocorticotropin</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>a growth
hormone produced by the anterior pituitary gland; it stimulates the
adrenal cortex.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> adrenocorticotropic hormone, adrenocorticotrophic
hormone, adrenocorticotrophin, corticotropin, corticotrophin,
ACTH</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

